WHAT IS THIS THING?
¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
HIT TILES 2 is a game based on the wellknown oriental game called Shanghai. It
consists of 15 levels, each one featuring a screen made up of 120 tiles placed
in piles up to 4 high. In every screen there are 4 of each tile. The aim of the
game is to remove all of the tiles from the screen. The main and only rule you
have to keep in mind is this: You can only remove 2 equals tiles at a time ad
both must have an empty place on either the left or the right hand side.



KEYS IN GAME
¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
Left mouse button to select the tile
Right mouse button to active help
Both mouse buttons to deselect the tile
P key to pause
M key to enable or disable the game music
Esc key or click on the top-left corner gadget to quit



FEATURES
¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
15 different levels
Useful HELP mode for beginners
Automatic check of a premature end-of-the-game (no more free tiles to remove)
32 colors screens
4 different modules
Superb SFX
Full game loaded at start on machines with 1Mb chip or more
Hi-scores saving
Possibility to load "new tiles-set" before to start



